# InsightDrop CLI – Docker Setup

Zero-persistence sales analytics pipeline. No FastAPI, no server — pure terminal.

---

## Project Structure

```
insightdrop/
├── insightdrop.py      ← CLI entry point
├── pipeline.py         ← ETL core
├── generate_data.py    ← sample data generator
├── requirements.txt
├── Dockerfile
├── docker-compose.yml
├── .dockerignore
├── data/               ← drop your CSV/XLSX files here
└── exports/            ← reports are written here
```

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Build the image (one time)
docker compose build

# 2. Generate 500-row sample data into data/sales.csv
docker compose run --rm insightdrop generate

# 3. Analyze and print results to terminal
docker compose run --rm insightdrop analyze data/sales.csv

# 4. Export to Excel  →  exports/
docker compose run --rm insightdrop export data/sales.csv --format excel

# 5. Export to PDF  →  exports/
docker compose run --rm insightdrop export data/sales.csv --format pdf
```

---

## All Commands

### Generate sample data
```bash
docker compose run --rm insightdrop generate
docker compose run --rm insightdrop generate --rows 1000
docker compose run --rm insightdrop generate --output data/q1_sales.csv
```

### Analyze (terminal output)
```bash
# Formatted tables + KPIs
docker compose run --rm insightdrop analyze data/sales.csv

# Raw JSON output
docker compose run --rm insightdrop analyze data/sales.csv --json

# Your own file (drop it in data/ first)
docker compose run --rm insightdrop analyze data/my_file.xlsx
```

### Export
```bash
# Excel (default) — 6 sheets: KPIs, Monthly, Products, Region, Category, Cleaned Data
docker compose run --rm insightdrop export data/sales.csv

# PDF report
docker compose run --rm insightdrop export data/sales.csv --format pdf

# Custom output filename (saved into exports/)
docker compose run --rm insightdrop export data/sales.csv --format pdf --out q1_report
```

### Convenience shortcuts (pre-wired in docker-compose.yml)
```bash
docker compose run --rm generate       # generate 500-row CSV
docker compose run --rm analyze        # analyze data/sales.csv
docker compose run --rm export-excel   # export to Excel
docker compose run --rm export-pdf     # export to PDF
```

---

## Use Your Own File

Drop any CSV or XLSX into the `data/` folder, then:
```bash
docker compose run --rm insightdrop analyze data/your_file.csv
docker compose run --rm insightdrop export  data/your_file.xlsx --format pdf
```

### Required columns (aliases accepted)

| Column         | Aliases                                  |
|----------------|------------------------------------------|
| `order_id`     | `orderid`, `order id`                    |
| `product_name` | `productname`, `product name`, `product` |
| `category`     | —                                        |
| `quantity`     | `qty`, `units`                           |
| `price`        | `unit_price`, `unit price`               |
| `cost`         | `unit_cost`, `unit cost`                 |
| `order_date`   | `date`, `sale_date`                      |
| `region`       | `area`, `zone`                           |

